{"cf_tracking_thunderbird_esr52": "---", "status": "RESOLVED", "cf_tracking_firefox60": "---", "cf_tracking_firefox61": "---", "cf_tracking_firefox62": "---", "creator": "alice0775@yahoo.co.jp", "mentors_detail": [], "depends_on": [1251257], "cf_status_firefox_esr60": "---", "cf_user_story": "", "cf_status_firefox56": "---", "cf_tracking_firefox_relnote": "---", "platform": "x86", "cf_status_firefox58": "---", "keywords": ["regression"], "cf_status_firefox57": "---", "summary": "[e10s] Images glitch  in sites that use a popular KenBurns slider with Disabled HWA on Ubuntu", "cf_last_resolved": "2016-03-18T15:10:28Z", "attachments": [{"creator": "edwin.bugs@flores.geek.nz", "is_obsolete": 0, "is_patch": 1, "flags": [{"status": "+", "name": "review", "modification_date": "2016-03-17T08:50:29Z", "type_id": 4, "creation_date": "2016-03-16T18:55:06Z", "id": 1361310, "setter": "nical.bugzilla@gmail.com"}], "content_type": "text/plain", "id": 8731372}], "votes": 0, "classification": "Components", "is_confirmed": true, "is_creator_accessible": true, "cf_has_regression_range": "---", "comment_count": 13, "comments": [{"text": "+++ This bug was initially created as a clone of Bug #1252275 Comment 5 +++\n\nBuild Identifier:\n\n\nReproducible : always\n\nSteps To Reproduce:\n1. e10s on + HWA off\n2. Open index.html from attachment 8725374\n   (original web page: http://wowslider.com/it/banner-maker-geometric-kenburns-demo.html )\n\n\nActual Results:\n Images glitch during animation\n Screencast : https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=2_1tMueQgxQ  (around20,25,34s)\n\nExpected results:\n No glitch\n\nRegression window on ubuntu14.04 (e10s on + HWA off):\nhttps://hg.mozilla.org/integration/mozilla-inbound/pushloghtml?fromchange=600942ae9823ae85186cd613b65582078489daa4&tochange=432ef38dab958e325c2e56dd4093be023c221043\n\nRegressed by: Bug 1241832", "author": "alice0775@yahoo.co.jp", "id": 11216242, "time": "2016-03-03T20:04:28Z"}, {"text": "Edwin, let's see if we can help get \"no xrender\" in a better state.", "author": "milaninbugzilla@gmail.com", "id": 11216719, "time": "2016-03-03T21:55:10Z"}, {"text": "This is probably the same bug as 1253995, but bug 1253995 has a nice test case attached!", "author": "mchang@mozilla.com", "id": 11225998, "time": "2016-03-08T00:05:26Z"}, {"text": "This happens to me in a non-e10s window.", "author": "bill.mccloskey@gmail.com", "id": 11229455, "time": "2016-03-08T21:53:53Z"}, {"text": "(In reply to Bill McCloskey (:billm) from comment #3)\n> This happens to me in a non-e10s window.\n\nI cannot reproduce with \"disabled e10s\".\nI think \"non-e10s window\" is not equal to \"disabled e10s\"", "author": "alice0775@yahoo.co.jp", "id": 11233330, "time": "2016-03-09T21:31:38Z"}, {"text": "I can reproduce this reliably Ubuntu 14.04, Nightly 48.0a1, 20160310030242 by mousing hovering around over the images that are being animated/swapped.\n\nI cannot reproduce if HWA is on nor in non-e10s.", "author": "twalker@mozilla.com", "id": 11235981, "time": "2016-03-10T16:32:03Z"}, {"text": "*** Bug 1252275 has been marked as a duplicate of this bug. ***", "author": "lsalzman@mozilla.com", "id": 11249534, "time": "2016-03-15T21:48:40Z"}, {"text": "Reposting findings from bug 1252275 here:\n\n\nI discussed with Edwin, Nical, and Matt regarding what we thought the underlying issue was and the best way to progress with a workaround in the short-term.\n\nThe issue seems to be a manifestation of bug 1251257, that we are overwriting the canvas client's buffer while the compositor is using it. This ends up causing tearing.\n\nMatt suspects that we should be fine just to double buffer the canvas client based on the refresh driver synchronization he had implemented here: http://mxr.mozilla.org/mozilla-central/source/layout/base/nsRefreshDriver.cpp#1647\n\nI tested a double-buffering prototype Edwin was working on both under Linux and Windows. I was able to reproduce the issue on both platforms without the patch, and with the patch, the problem was fixed on both platforms.\n\nArguably we might want to fix this under bug 1251257, or perhaps save bug 1251257 for a long-term solution (if desired and if differs from short-term fix) and go with a short-term fix in this bug.", "author": "lsalzman@mozilla.com", "id": 11249553, "time": "2016-03-15T21:51:44Z"}, {"text": "*** Bug 1252046 has been marked as a duplicate of this bug. ***", "author": "mchang@mozilla.com", "id": 11249759, "time": "2016-03-15T22:43:31Z"}, {"text": "Created attachment 8731372\nhmmmmmmm\n\nThis will work, according to bug 1252275 comment 9.", "author": "edwin.bugs@flores.geek.nz", "id": 11252840, "time": "2016-03-16T18:55:06Z"}, {"text": "https://hg.mozilla.org/integration/mozilla-inbound/rev/705f2b00c129", "author": "pulsebot@bots.tld", "id": 11254939, "time": "2016-03-17T11:12:13Z"}, {"text": "https://hg.mozilla.org/mozilla-central/rev/705f2b00c129", "author": "cbook@mozilla.com", "id": 11259018, "time": "2016-03-18T15:10:28Z"}, {"text": "e10s will be disabled on release for 47. It is still enabled in beta 47 for some of the beta population. So I'm marking this as wontfix for 47.", "author": "lhenry@mozilla.com", "id": 11434099, "time": "2016-05-24T23:36:41Z"}], "id": 1253386, "priority": "P5", "cc": ["alice0775@yahoo.co.jp", "bill.mccloskey@gmail.com", "brad@lassey.us", "epinal99-bugzilla2@yahoo.fr", "flavio@fellah.us", "jmathies@mozilla.com", "jmuizelaar@mozilla.com", "karlt@mozbugz.karlt.net", "lsalzman@mozilla.com", "mchang@mozilla.com", "milaninbugzilla@gmail.com", "nical.bugzilla@gmail.com", "nissan4321@gmail.com", "twalker@mozilla.com"], "cf_crash_signature": "", "version": "47 Branch", "is_cc_accessible": true, "cf_tracking_firefox_esr52": "---", "see_also": ["https://bugzilla.mozilla.org/show_bug.cgi?id=1252046", "https://bugzilla.mozilla.org/show_bug.cgi?id=1253995", "https://bugzilla.mozilla.org/show_bug.cgi?id=1254560", "https://bugzilla.mozilla.org/show_bug.cgi?id=1254318"], "cf_tracking_thunderbird_esr60": "---", "cf_